<subSubSection id="C322DFC5281DFF8C8CE7B203FD2AFA63" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B878C4E281DFF8C8CE7B203FD2AFA63" blockId="6.[151,1437,1370,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281DFF8C8CE7B203FED5FAAB" bold="true" box="[151,266,1370,1396]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F7CD281DFF8C8D6EB203FEA8FAAB" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1818" box="[286,375,1370,1396]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281DFF8C8D6EB203FEA8FAAB" box="[286,375,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Chloeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with ventral cirri of similar size throughout body; bipinnate branchiae from chaetiger 4; middorsal spots with a median constriction, surrounded by a circular pale area over a darker background, projected as lateral bands; chaetal bundles homogeneously pale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322DFC5281DFF8C8CB7B29EFC83F8FB" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B878C4E281DFF8C8CB7B29EFC83F8FB" blockId="6.[151,1437,1370,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281DFF8C8CB7B29EFEE4FA3E" bold="true" box="[199,315,1479,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Remarks.</emphasis>
No specimens were studied; Horst 
<typeStatus id="548332EC281DFF8C8EA7B29EFCD8FA3E" box="[727,775,1479,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">type</typeStatus>
specimens are deposited in Leiden, but this 
<typeStatus id="548332EC281DFF8C897AB29EFAE5FA3E" box="[1290,1338,1479,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">type</typeStatus>
was not listed in the corresponding catalogue (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281DFF8C8E37B2B3FC7AF9DA" author="Bleeker, J. &amp; van der Spoel, S." box="[583,933,1514,1541]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="121 - 166" refId="ref21631" refString="Bleeker, J. &amp; van der Spoel, S. (1992) Catalogue of the Polychaeta collected by the Siboga Expedition and type specimens of Polychaeta in the Zoological Museum of Amsterdam. Bulletin Zoologischen Museum, Universiteit van Amsterdam, 13, 121 - 166." type="journal article" year="1992">Bleeker &amp; van der Spoel 1992</bibRefCitation>
). However, the original description provides complete details and illustration of the pigmentation pattern, which resembles a horseshoe with a middorsal line medially constricted on each segment. No specimens from tropical American seas show this pigmentation pattern. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281DFF8C8D7DB10FFE11F9AE" author="Fauvel, P." box="[269,462,1622,1649]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref23004" refString="Fauvel, P. (1943) Annelides polychetes de Californie recueillies par L. Diguet. Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 18, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1943">Fauvel (1943: 7)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F7CD281DFF8C8E33B10EFD07F9AF" authorityName="Horst" authorityYear="1910" box="[579,728,1623,1649]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="conspicua">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281DFF8C8E33B10EFD07F9AF" box="[579,728,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">C. conspicua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="49FC42AC281DFF8C8FE6B10FFBD7F9AF" box="[918,1032,1622,1648]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">California</collectingRegion>
and he indicated that (transl.) “the dorsal surface has two thin longitudinal pale bands separating three other wider, brown reddish bands, that are modified in each segment into a slightly wider medial band ahead of two slightly oblique lateral bands, and more or less fused basally below the median band. This outlook is very similar to the dorsal pattern of a 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F7CD281DFF8C88C0B19BFAD6F903" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1818" box="[1200,1289,1730,1756]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281DFF8C88C0B19BFAD6F903" box="[1200,1289,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Chloeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Taboga illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281DFF8C8D45B1BEFE33F8DE" author="Monro, C. C. A." box="[309,492,1767,1793]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref24599" refString="Monro, C. C. A. (1933) The Polychaeta Errantia collected by Dr. C. Crossland at Colon, in the Panama Region, and the Galapagos Islands during the Expedition of the S. Y. ' St. George'. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, 1933 (1), 1 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1933. tb 01578. x" type="journal article" year="1933">Monro (1933: 9</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130390CB281DFF8C8D89B1BFFD9FF8DE" box="[505,576,1766,1793]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1669,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,183,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chloeia euglochis Ehlers, 1887, reinstated. A. Syntype complete (MCZ ANNa-720), dorsal view. B. Same, illustration from Ehlers (1887). C. Same, extract from Haeckel’s plates (1904, Pl. 96). D. Another syntype (MCZ ANNa-3), oblique lateral view. E. Notochaeta. F, G. Neurochaetae (from Ehlers 1887) (Photo: D, Elizabeth Borda)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479997" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479997/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
)”. As indicated below, Monro’s record corresponds with 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F7CD281DFF8C88BDB1BEFEE0F8FA" authority="Augener, 1922" authorityName="Augener" authorityYear="1922" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pseudeuglochis">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281DFF8C88BDB1BEFA42F8DF" box="[1229,1437,1766,1793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">C. pseudeuglochis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281DFF8C8CE7B052FEE0F8FA" author="Augener, H." box="[151,319,1803,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="38 - 53" refId="ref21238" refString="Augener, H. (1922) Ueber litorale Polychaeten von Westindien. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 1922 (3 - 5), 38 - 53." type="journal article" year="1922">Augener, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and Fauvel’s record is listed under that species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
